reviews.text: Absolutely love this place! We’ve been coming here for years. They always have fantastic exhibits that are free to the public and special exhibits as well. They also have a lot of events inspired by the artist on exhibit, for example, the make and take event inspired by Jonas Wood where people were given 6x6 canvas and paint and create their own artwork. Late night at the museum events are always fun too! Highly recommend for the whole family!

We were invited to an event a few years ago, and took part in a couple class type events. One was taught by a published children's author and artist. It was a great experience which led my artist son and I to take this to our own community, and share it with others for many opportunities during the following years. A great museum of art. Loved the gift store.

I brought my kids here for the first time and it was a wonderful experience.  RAMONA (I believe; last name Miller maybe) took our experience to the next level; and honestly gave me a new level of appreciation for all of the beautiful art this museum had to offer.  Antoine (pardon my spelling) informed me of the Dior show coming at the end of May so I cannot wait to go back.  Awesome staff, beautiful art, and a great time.  

I almost forgot to mention the free arts and crafts my children got to partake in as well!

I have recently started getting more into art. The Dallas Museum of Art is hands down the best of the 10 or so comparable art museums I have been to. Per usual, you should check what they have on display prior to going to make sure it aligns with your interests, but nonetheless it is a fantastic way to spend a handful of hours. Plus it is free.

Just got home excited to hear my family tell me how their visit to the museum went. Well lets just say i only gave it a star because my kids did crafts and it was free. 
As for my wife and mom well they were encountered by some rude employees. Will definitely never go here again and will not recommend it.

Amazing! It's not only an aquarium but a zoo as well. They had exotic birds, sharks, sloths, alligators, sting rays... everything! They layout was perfect. You start at the top floor and work your way down moving through several countries across the globe. My kids loved this place!

What a delightful surprise this beautiful aquarium is. Actually, it's more than an aquarium, it's a rain forest, mini zoo, and more. I love nature and the rain forest environment is so beautiful and a feast for the eyes.. Of course, the animals were just delightful as well. The underwater life is also incredible especially the manatee. I urge everyone to go see and support this wonderful Dallas attraction

I went here and brought my sister and her BF because we love seeing animals. The title is misleading as this is more of a zoo than aquarium..or both..? The reason for 2 stars is because we had to wait in line outside in order to purchase our ticket. Okay no big deal, most places like this you do. BUT waiting in line as you make your way throughout the aquarium... never before have I had to do this. Yes I understand crowds and such but the layout is very narrow when it's very crowded. We stood in line for maybe 25 to 30 minutes and then inside while trying to see animals a good 10 minutes before the line even moved. Stroller took up walkways. People standing in the walk way blocking traffic. There was no room to go around or anything. I honestly thought this would be a great experience but it sucked. I disliked it and for the price we paid, was not worth the money in my opinion.

Great selection of fish, birds and animals. Can be quite crowded sometimes but it isn't unbearable. The exhibits tanks are clean and well maintained. Has outdoorsy jungle-like areas as well as the completely indoor areas where the fish tanks are housed. Also has a small underwater tunnel where you can view various sea fauna. The collection of fish from different parts of the world is extensive, well-curated and comprehensively documented.

It's nice to come to the aquarium now and then, and after not being for a while, it was nice to see that they've seemed to relax their prices a bit. The exhibits are just as interesting as they've always been. The amount of people can be overwhelming at times but there are spurts where you can visit some of the exhibits without having to fight to see. For a unique experience I'd highly recommend coming here

Great learning environment for kids. Some of the information on certain displays (astronomy, energy generation and extraction) need updating with our current understanding of these fields. Nonetheless great for those just getting into or with an interest of natural sciences. My recommendation is ages 4+ if as a parent you want your child interested in the experience. Still great for families of all ages. My personal favorite was the gemstones and minerals exhibit. The staff was kind and helpful.

The building itself is a work of art and inventive architecture! We visited during summer of 2018 and particularly enjoyed the geological display.  They have a massive geode that can be opened and closed via a crank wheel.  Otherwise the displays are highly interactive and will keep you and your crew busy for hours.  My kiddos were 6 and 9 and had a blast.  I rarely give five stars and didn't for this review either but the museum is very close to deserving that extra star.

Amazing place for all ages. 4 levels of interactive and fun exhibits plus the lower level has a fun sports area where you can do some interactive science related sports activities and a children's museum. If you are planning on attending March through first part of June which is when we were there than there are MANY kids running around the entire facility as schools do their field trips this time of year. But for a small fee you can fill up almost an entire day here. Definitely a must do for families if you are in the area

This place is amazing. Visited from out of state with 5 year old kids and they loved every minute of it. They recommend starting on the fourth floor and working your way down. Follow that advice and you'll have a great time. The dinosaur bones and exhibits on the fourth floor were my son's favorite and the gems and minerals on the third were my daughter's. There's no way to see everything in one visit without spending all day in the museum.

Was there today for a birthday party. The room attendants were great and had lots of fun activities for the children. My favorite was the old vinegar/baking soda volcano eruption. As part of the birthday party you got access to the museum after the party ended. Which was a very nice touch. We will go back when we have more time to explore!

They are building a new museum right across the street from the current museum that maybe well worth the visit.  The current museum was on one floor with photos and some artifacts from the Holocaust.  You received a listening device that you had to punch in corresponding numbers to hear about what happened in the photo.  Very interesting, but I hope that they have more actual stuff in the new museum when it opens.

A very good coverage of the Holocaust which provides insight into how good people can do evil things when led by a bully who demonizes those who are "not like us."  The audio self-guided tour gives you the option of skimming or deeply studying each of the areas in the museum.  One could easily spend over 4 hours without covering it all.

I know much of the Holocaust history,  but these exhibits are sobering and informative.  1 1/2 hours was not long enough.  Well worth $10.  Please don't bring children who are too young to understand and appreciate this.  Some photos very graphic.

I've been wanting to check out this museum for years and I finally made time for it today. I really enjoyed it.  The wonderful artifacts and photos really helped me to put myself in the place of the victims of this tragedy.  Handheld audio devices explained everything of interest to me.  The place is pretty small but they make good use of the area.  Overall, it was a truly educational experience.
I really enjoyed it. They need more space. The new building looks great from the outside and will give them more room. Definitely worth seeing.
No answers to any phone calls AND when you get to leave a message - they hang up on you. Dallas NEEDS a better phone system ...or someone to ANSWER the phones.
For removing the Confederate monuments. Put it to a vote. I will not visit Dallas anymore until they remove this Marxist city council.
If you call no one answers and when you visit they are rude.... Who the hell voted these ppl in office, bcuz I didn't. Ugh I wish everyone would go to the ballot

Never ever ever ever valet park. It will literally take 2 hrs to get your car. I've been waiting outside for 2hrs. Plus there is no where to sit on the inside . I will never come back here.

Tell me why we showed up one Friday there was maybe 10 ppl in the club, at 11;45ish, the next day a Saturday there was still NO LINE and they were charging 15 a piece at the door with these MIB security guards everywhere. They’re only poppin like EVERY OTHER Saturday, we’ve had a good time here before but it’s like a miss, miss, miss, hit. Cause Ive been here maybe 10 times and 25% of the time there was actually ppl inside
This is a nice club with a great atmosphere but the loud music left me and my friends ears ringing. Also, the flashing/strobing, seizure inducing lights made me physically sick after a while.

Visited this nice little spot for the first time this past weekend. It's seriously stylish and the music was great! The vibe was cool, people were well dressed and the drinks were pretty cheap. Valet was only $8 but it took forever to get the car once we were ready to go. I would definitely visit again! Great night out. Oh yeah, the lighting on the dance floor and the artwork is seriously DOPE, very very nice touch.

Awesome venue, with a really neat lighting system. The staff was friendly and made me feel welcome. The artwork in the venue is Instagram worthy and the bottle presentations are something like Vegas nightlife. This place gives Dallas a whole new feel, the space is glam and over the top in a good way. This place is surely to blow up.
Absolutely the bomb . com :) 3 friends shared each other's order. ALL food was delicious! Even chips & avocado dip  we're fresh and delicious! Will definitely visit on next trip to Dallas!

Very good food! The food comes surprisingly fast for such a fancy restaurant. The wait staff is attentive and accommodating. The food tastes very fresh. The lighting is a bit dark but other than that it is a great venue in an easy to get to and friendly location.

Had brunch with my girlfriends on a Sunday afternoon. Staff was friendly. They don't have a brunch menu only serves dinner menu. So if you are looking for eggs, try a different place. Price is a little on the more expensive side because it's the dinner menu. Their salsa is good, it has chunks of avocado in it. Their skinny margarita was good. Again still on the pricer side. Parking is paid meter only. Can be difficult to park during peak hours. Not sure if they offer valet.

Really nice restaurant!! The dining area was very clean and stylish. The staff was super nice. Our waiter was new but he did a wonderful job!!
The food tasted amazing!! 
I ordered the chicken tortilla soup and wanted to drink the whole pot!!
The salsa was spicy but not too much and they put avocados in the salsa!! Whoah!!
Super yummy!! Will definitely go back.

Went for lunch, great patio seating. I had the grilled chicken salad. My chicken was too grilled for my liking but not bad, just a preference thing. The salad was great it had grilled nopales , pickled red onions and some other deliciousness. Their guacamole was fab, and their salsa is really good! Juan was our waiter and he was very accommodating,  and even shook our hands on departure. We are clearly best friends now.

Beats the pants off of olive garden. But then again,  ketchup on lasagna noodles beats olive garden. It's a really cool place inside. There's a train car, and an elevator table and a few other cool places to eat. Not what you'd expect from a chain restaurant. Prices are very fair and service is always top notch. Ask for Jimmy if you can. He's so personable and doesn't just treat you like another table. Where else can you get spaghetti with meatballs, a piece of delicious sweet Italian sausage, and crispy garlic bread for only $14? Parking is a breeze and its laid out so that even when it's crowded, you're not right on top of people.

Used to love going here with my grandparents when I was young. The food tastes different now but the atmosphere is the same. My kids like it here because there is always something to look at and the bread is still really good.

Great place for larger group lunches during the work day or a neat place to have dinner on the weekend.  They accommodated our party of 10 for lunch, we were served in a timely manner and the food was great.   Ive also attended a retirement luncheon here with 50+ people and the experience was usual.   Ample servers assigned, food came out hot and was still great.

Lose yourself in this unique Italian restaurant... sample their sourdough bread with the amazing butter spread. Order some pasta to fill up on... and to top it off. A divine piece of Italian cream torte... I'm salivating just thinking about it! Or go for the more traditional cheesecake... ☆☆☆☆ definitely the flavor overload you were looking for!

The only thing good about this restaurant was the decor. It was very unique inside with a trolley car. It wasn't packed when we went so the service should be spot on. It wasn't as we all waited 15 min for drinks and I waited 30 additional min for my adult beverage... Food wasn't great either. My lasagna was just sauce and pasta with hardly any meat on it. Didn't really taste great either. It seemed like teenagers were running the place and they didn't seem like they wanted to be there. Will never go back... Had better Italian food at Angie's Italian restaurant in Barberton.
excellent spot to spend time alone or talk business. the service here is better than most. bring your hunger - portions are large. i see why this place has so many great reviews.

We 3 (Hubby, Son & I) go once a year on my Husband's Birthday.  We enjoy the ambiance, the staff are very nice, the silverware always looks new and clean.  The cheese plate of appetizers is absolutely delicious. I always order the same chicken and potatoes cooked to perfection (the way my Son cooks it).  My Son loves that his Steak is as rare as his request.  And Hubby loved the Lobster and was happy We returned as we do each year for his Birthday.
Great Food and service. Went family style today with friends. Dry aged Ribeye was the best. Liked the wine and dessert menu.

We had a wonderful dinner at Dallas Chop House.  The service was on point, the drinks were great, and the steaks were cooked to perfection.  They really seem to take care in providing the best cuts of meat and cooking them exactly how the customer prefers.  Good job to everyone there.
Really enjoyed the meal.  Restaurant is a bit dated, but staff very helpful and pleasant.  Definitely revisit for special occasions.

Had brunch for the first time! Brunch menu was delicious and just right amount of food! Sat at the bar. Great and friendly service. Love the bean dip that comes to the table with chips and salsa. Brunch food came out fast. I definitely will come back for brunch again and will highly recommend this place to friends and family.

This place is great! It has a hint of authenticity with the tad of flair. Staff is super nice and they wear these fancy little shirts. I've never gone to this place and felt disappointed with my food. Even if I tried something new. It may not have been what I wanted or was in the mood for but it never let me down. They have a couple of pretty good drinks too. Check them out! I doubt you'll be disappointed!

Gloria's is one of my favorite restaurants and this location was not my usual location to go. Food tasted great as I expected. I enjoyed the Salsa dancing after the restaurant hours at this location. We didn't wait too long to get seated on a Friday night for a party of 10. I decided to try something different this time.and it tasted good. Yucca and plantain.

This restaurant apparently is "the" place to be on a Friday night for dinner and dancing. Once the guests have finished eating, they sit and talk. Large parties must wait until 80% of everyone is there before being seated. (understandingly) Parking is difficult because of the other restaurants in the same area. But, it's a very good experience. 👍

My favorite Latin dance joint. I like that it switches back and forth between the live salsa band and the DJ mix. It gives you a nice variation of dancing for everyone. I would definitely dress well to come to this location. Last I remember they do have a dress code, at least for the late night dancing they certainly do. In terms of the food service, the food is hit or miss honestly. It used to be a lot better 8-10 years ago, but I feel there have been a lot of changes and the food just isn't quite what it used to be. I recommend the pupusas, the fajita nachos, and the Salvadorian sampler/mix plate (I can't remember exactly what it's called). The drinks are definitely better than the food here so make sure to order a margarita or cocktail drink as that is their strong suit. You don't need more than 2 to have a great evening.
Very good Japanese restaurant. Great food and loads of options, all very tasty.

This little place is hard to beat. The chirashi sushi lunch set was a generous portion, high in quality, including the rice, and very fair in price.  The side dishes were equally good.  The service was prompt and friendly. I will be back to try some of their other dishes.
Food Fresh and People friendly
Great food. Slightly pricey
Great quality of menu, excellent service. Highly Recommended.

I wasn't really a fan of the food here. I ordered fruit crepes, and the egg flavor was too much for me. Then, I got pancakes and they weren't cooked thoroughly. I didn't complain because I'd already sent my crepes back and my server was so sweet and accommodating.

Always good food and service when I come here. If you're a coffee lover, you'll be in love with the variety of choice brews they have available.  I always order the same thing..lol..classic breakfast.  Can't go wrong with bacon and eggs.

i got the nachos as a starter they were excellent (as usual), pancakes were fluffy ... eggs left something to be desired.  all in all good spot. 
however NO GRITS

Great coffee and pretty good service. They get pretty busy sometimes, and can forget items you ordered, but the wait staff is pleasant. The food is usually good, with vegan and gluten free options available. Parking is easy and convenient. The bottomless coffee is well worth it.
Chicken and Waffles at 3:00 am are amazing! It is a great atmosphere, delicious food, friendly staff and open late. What could be better!?!

This has become one of my favorite spots after just two visits. I went for dinner the first time and fell in love with the grit tots and biscuits with honey butter. Amazing start to my meal and the shrimp and grits entree was also incredible. My fiancé had steak which was also very well prepared and juicy. Second time we had brunch and it was amazing! The chicken and waffles were a generous portion with a delicious hot sauce. The French toast had great texture and flavor. I would highly recommend the biscuits and grit tots, must try if you dine here.

This place is assume and the food is great. A nice spin on the hot sauce. I had the shrimp and grits nice size shrimps and grits soft and the seasoning great. I'm from Charleston SC, so I know what good food taste like. 
I could go on and on but you gotta go there and see for yourself.

Have had brunch here twice, both times were excellent. After a night of partying, its hard to beat chicken n waffles with a mimosa. The biscuits are always warm out of the oven, and the gravy was pretty good. The chicken & waffles is a great deal for under $20, its a ton of food that will set you on a path to Deep Couch City. I am salivating just thinking about it.

All of the food was fresh, creative, flavorful and delicious.  The cocktails we're excellent as well.  It has a rustic farmhouse vibe which compliments the southern themed menu.  The atmosphere was lively and energetic and the bar has a unique design with a decent amount of seating.

Go for a good brunch experience. Great food and soothing ambience. 
Must try— Short rib hash and biscuits.

The park was beautiful and very relaxing despite the large crowds. It was a great way to spend the afternoon. The only reason it is not 5 starts is because admission and parking price was much more than expected. We ended up only being able to spend an hour and a half in the park and still paid full price for parking and Festival price for admission. 

I would defiantly go back, but I would make sure to go right when they opened to get the full experience and my moneys worth.

The tulips were gorgeous. I loved seeing all the beautiful landscapes and views of the lake. The many trails with the historic home and many gardens to enjoy was breathtaking. It is a great place to spend a day just relaxing and enjoying nature. You can stop off and enjoy a meal or snack during your visit at one of the several kiosks or cafes. I had a wonderful time.

Wow! I have not been here in nearly a decade. The garden offers so much more than just a stroll through the flora and fauna. From Interactive STEM activities to a peaceful calming area to well, stroll through the tulips. The place has so much to offer. Of course check the weather and dress accordingly. Outside food and beverages were permitted.

I buy a season pass every year. It gives me free parking and early admittance into the Arboretum during the summer hours. This is the only way to go. Early mornings are amazing here. Peaceful and serene, and perfect for a brief respite from the concrete jungle of the city. I've also been able to shoot a plethora of beautiful flower photos here. I highly recommend Dallas Arboretum =)

Beautiful gardens and they've done a lot of improvements lately. They have a new kitchen where they hold classes and demonstrations. They have more water features and they are gorgeous! This is a very easy garden to walk and many different types of gardens. The degolyer house is also on the property and is  really nice to tour. They also have special events especially around the holidays in the home. There's also restaurants and afternoon tea, which is very good, but pricey. It's beautiful all seasons of the year. They have many special events. The prices can be high, but if you are remember you get a reduced rate. It is definitely worth becoming a member because it cost $15 to park and $15 to get in. You will recoup your money within a couple of visits. You also get special invitations to members only events and previews for public events.

I was most impressed with the 9/11 presentation, going through the President's day and seeing his Chief of Staff diary of what transpired. Chilling, and sad, but very well done. You get a feeling of his personality with all the family comments and pictures. I came away impressed with the entire Bush family, though I didn't vote for them! Parking costs $ but is across the street. gift shop and cafe available too.

The grounds and building are beautiful. The biggest plus about this place are the staff. They are so enthusiastic and passionate. They love to talk to visitors and answer questions. Great job hiring people. This library also had a great section on 9/11 and Bush's paintings highlighting the sacrifices our veterans have made is cool!

After visiting a good number of Presidential libraries, this is second only to President Reagan.  You have full access to the Oval Office.  The timeline of his presidency especially the events of 9/11 are deeply moving.  His daughters have done a wonderful and fun exhibit.  This is a must.

This was our first time visiting a presidential museum. Lots of great things to see. Parking was an ease but then again it wasn't as busy in the early morning. It was spring break for my kids so I am sure if it was spring break here as one lady had asked if my kids were on spring break.

The exhibits are really cool. They definitely had an exhibit from 9/11. They even had some steel beams from one of the towers. Brought some sad and memorable times during that as I was deployed during this time.

They have the oval office where you can sit and pretend to be the president. If you purchase more than one photo its pretty reasonable for the price.

Access to it from the highway was a breeze. There are plenty of restaurants close to by choose and eat from. They even have a cafe located at the entrance of the museum so you don't have to travel far if you don't want to.

Don't forget to download the app during your self guided tour.

We purchased the City Pass. I highly recommend it if you're interested in seeing the rest of Dallas. For family five it was $190 with tax. If you're not fast at sight seeing you have up to nine days to use the pass. My family and I were able to see everything in one day.

The staff were very friendly and fast. I definitely want to come back again.

Well built and thought out. George W. is the focus throughout. It made me realize he was well intentioned and had good morals. Lots of technology to use and enjoy, the museum is interactive. The 9/11 exhibit is moving, as is the info on Katrina and the federal response. Their Oval Office that you can explore is really cool.

Class of 2001 mane say jakk if u was there from 1997-2001 holla great school had fun shout out to Coach Landy she was a good gym teacher. Plus it was a good school. Made me appreciate different races and become the best black male that I became to be. Thank u so much I'm going to miss those days. 1997-2001 let's eat greedy people
the kids here got the best drugs i give em 10/10, but the atmosphere over all is trash and the rules they try to enforce dont do smack

This is among the worst schools I've ever been in.  During my freshman year, we didn't have a teacher for my computer class.  Then about a month into school, we got a teacher who didn't know anything.  In February, we got a teacher who knew the stuff, but by then, most of the students were horrible.  They were really awful to him.  He didn't give up though.  I know he wrote up some of the worst kids, but nothing ever happened to them, and they laughed about it.  I talked to kids in his engineering class who told me he was a teacher who cared about his students, but he didn't come back the next year.  There a lot of new teachers each year.  They need to do something about the kids who disrupt; they are trying to get into suspension.
The heater in some classrooms doesn't  work and is extremely hard for me to be successful when I can't stop feeling cold....
Horrible enrollment process. Unprepared and unconcerned with parents time. Need to do better!!!!!
Excellent food. I recommend the Enchiladas Rojas, personally. The ambiance was great, as was the service. And, get a load of the patio; the epitome of the outdoor dining experience. Well done.

Had late lunch there.  Perfect weather for sitting at their "in and out" tables.  It's covered but the large sliding glass partition was open so it's like being outside without the sun beating down on you.  Food was outstanding and the service was great.  It was my second time there and I will definitely be returning!

I can't say we will be back. Choose this place because of the reviews. Not impressed at all. I made reservations for 7:15 pm on Saturday night. I walked up to the host, no welcoming or anything. I had to speak up and say I had a reservation. The host said they were getting my table ready, it was 7:25 pm when I asked. So, I waited a bit longer because they were just sitting people left and right. I didn't get a follow up so I walked up again by that time it was 7:40 pm. I asked again for my table & I was told they are now getting ready. I said is this the way reservations are handled. she said well we are super busy and were trying to do the best we can. NOT okay! Table was finally ready and we sat down by 7:55 pm. We were sat in a space so tight we should have just sat with the table behind us. Our waitress was not friendly at all, she just seemed more overwhelmed than anything. She would disappear so much. We had to ask for refills, chips and salsa. Food was okay. My beans were so hard I probably could hit someone with it. She was bothered because she had to split up up our tickets. Let's just say it wasn't a good experience and we won't return.

Very trendy and slightly upscale feel. Great patio and very nice bar area. Food was very good and very filling. We split an entree and some queso and had food left over. I love that my beer came with a frozen glass and was ice cold. Their three piece chips and salsa was very unique and quiet tasty. Highly recommend for a night out.
Great food and wonderful service.  Save room for the carrot cake!   It's served warm with a delightful cinnamon infused whipped cream and pecans.  Super yummy!

I love this place with all my heart and soul. The food is always amazing as well as the employees. There is only one problem and it is that my order is always wrong. Call or order in person I am always missing something/given one order wrong, given less of what I've ordered, or getting extremely spicy food when I asked for it not to be spicy. I've spent close to or over $1,000 here and I've given up on believing my order is correct, but the food is too good not to come back. If I have to check my food visually and taste test it every time I'll gladly do it, I just wish I didn't have to.

The food and staff are great and friendly. Whenever I come here with my partner we tend to get a party platter, you get a little bit of a lot of things and it always fills us up. It's great if you are looking for a variety of items but don't want to order too much.

We were invited by our friend to have dinner. Food was horrible. Waiters they don't know what they were serving. They need more crew. They even missed the order. we ordered lamb curry, Thali, chicken tikka masala.
I will not recommend ruin our trip all the way from Santa Rosa.

this is my current favourite Indian restaurant. the dinner menu has a good selection, and the food is great. they also have a wider array of naan-like options than any other place i have tried. the parking lot is cramped and can be difficult to navigate.
The food is fresh and plentiful. The restaurant is easy to get to. The food is good.

Good food 🥘 Veg spring rolls 🤤 I have ordered Basil Fried Rice 🍛, the taste is okay. I didn’t feel like good sticky rice 🍚 and it tasted normal. Taste can be improved a bit better for fried rices. Overall experience is good. Ambiance and Service is very good. Nice to visit in a while.

Lunch was really very tasty -- green curry chicken.  This should have been a quick 45 minute lunch.  But after 20 minutes waiting for our order and not getting the attention of our waitress,  we had to get up and ask where was our order, only to find out that the waitress lost our order and didn't remember what we ordered so she had to ask for it again.  So service is below par and way slow, the decor and menus have seen their better day, but the food was tasty.
ordered the spicy crispy soy beef with brown rice. large servings, great taste and reasonable prices. will visit again while in Addison
Drop by for a quick work day dinner, ordered spicy stir fried flat noodle.  4.5 star service, 3 star food. Reasonable price, Willing to try other dish next time hoping better taste

Delicious, quick, and (usually) accurate and friendly. Fantastic vegan proteins. The one thing I would suggest is working on your noodle dishes, that section of the menu is a bit bland compared to everything else.
One of my favorite places for tasty Chinese food. It was so tasty. The service here is better than most. Prices were reasonable. I see why this place has a lot of great reviews.

Good for delivery Chinese food. Their sesame sauce is super good. Love the hot and sour soup. Is it the best I ever had no. Is it good for quick lunch or your craving Chinese and want it delivered yes. It does take time for delivery.

Well where to start,  we ordered a Coke and a Dr. Pepper.  We got 2 glasses of ice and two cans of soda. Wow! The food is edible however I have certainly had much better but I have also had worse. Would I recommend this restaurant or will I be returning? NO!
Great place for tasty Chinese food. Got there near five, it wasn't very busy. Next time I'll be back with my relatives. Prices are fair.
Clean place, good Chinese (I recommend the steamed pork dumplings), and decent service. Mostly a take out place, but comfortable enough if you want to eat in.
My preferred place for delicious bbq. Service is always prompt even when they have a full house. Service treated us so kindly. Makes me feel like I in Nashville again.

This comes done to personal pallet. For me the brisket was too fatty, the fried okra tasted like it was made in old grease, and the mashed potatoes were standard.

The staff was on point, as the food and drinks came out promptly.
BBQ and the feeling at this location is great. One of the best spots in the area. Next time I'll be back with my coworkers. The bill won't shock you.

This will be VERY hard for the other BBQ joints we're visiting to beat. The ribs were perfect, their coleslaw was the best we've ever tasted and we were glad we took Toya's recommendation to save room for a fried cherry pie. Outstanding... and we're picky.
BBQ at this place - super good. Staff is always super even when they have a full house. There was quick, helpful, and friendly service. The place has a great feel to it.
All the basic BBQ fare.  Well prepared. Decent prices. Quick service.  A good neighborhood place, but I wouldn't drive too far to get there.

In all the years I've been going to this Sony Bryan's location, I have never been disappointed. Mostly I do take out. .on way home. Service is always great, order never wrong, food hot and fresh. Have used them for catering as well..two personal parties and two neighborhood HOA gatherings. Finally.... delicious.  That's most important.

My company used them to cater their Thanksgiving luncheon this past month for 400+ people and it turned out great! I received so many compliments on the quality of the food.  I also would like to say that the customer service I received from the beginning of process of my catering event was awesome all the way to the end of my event.  They made it smooth and I did not have one problem.  This would have been my 2nd year using them. And this was for sure the best year yet! I can't wait to use them again!
Love the service and lunch suggestion. The turkey was an excellent choice, smokey, tender and yummy.
The food was good, and the staff very friendly. I had the crispy chicken salad.

Fantastic store for authentic Italian foods and  amazing sandwiches. There is typically a line for the sandwiches, but they are well worth it. The sandwiches are  made fresh with quality ingredients for reasonable prices. While waiting for our sandwiches, it gives us time to check out the authentic Italian grocery items and the decor. The only bad thing about this place is the parking, which can be difficult when they are busy.

Who would have thought you could find an authentic Italian market in East Dallas?! I've been in love with this place ever since I moved to DFW, and will continue to support it as long as we're both around. There's no better place in town to pick up Italian meats and cheeses, wines, pastas, etc. And the deli also serves delicious sandwiches, just expect a bit of a line/wait during the lunch rush

Go the back counter and order the Italian stallion. Or order anything else on the sandwich menu. They are all good. Or just go in for smells. The place smells wonderful. The aroma of the marinara is great. Get cheese, olive oil, and everything else Italian here. Worth the drive.

Quaint on the outside, but large on the inside with delicacies of the meat and sauce variety. Fresh cookies from New Jersey, fruits, sandwiches made to order, wines and outdoor as well as indoor places to eat and read. Friendly staff. Good place to explore. Authentic Italian.
Jimmy's is a culinary wonderland! I couldn't believe how good it smelled in there and the Italian beef sandwich was incredible! I can't wait to come back again!

3.16.2019
My fiancé and I are from out of town. We asked a local to recommend an Italian place and they suggested Campisi’s. So glad we went! It was fabulous! The atmosphere was perfect. It felt both romantic and calming! The food was phenomenal! And the price is great for what you get. Thank you for a wonderful evening.

I've eaten at several different Campisi's over the years and I'm just not whelmed.  Just now I had fettuccine Alfredo and it was quite probably the blandest Alfredo sauce I've ever had.  There was no garlic, no onion, no seasoning at all (not even salt or pepper). It literally tasted like someone mixed unsalted butter with flour into a pan to make a roux and added heavy cream.  I've had the pizza and I don't remember specifically what I didn't like about, just that I didn't want to have to eat it again.

The food was hot, the service is good, and the orders were correct, but the taste was just not there.

Love this restaurant.  Have been to most of their chain restaurants, love the original Egyptian Room location best.  Only thing different about this one is you order your food at a counter instead of being waited on at your table.  Food is still excellent.  Love their all the way pizzas with thin crist.
I have not been to Campisis in awhile and wow.... delivery was quick, driver smiled.   The pizza was super hot and one of the best pies I’ve had in Dallas in months!

Pretty good Italian food.   Order at the counter...so unless they screw up your order, you don't need to worry about service.   Not a full Campisi's menu available here, no bar service....but up can BYOB.   Apps are very good....I make 2 meals out of sausage n peppers.   Pizzas are outstanding.   Looking for a quick Italian fix or great pizza....dont pass on Campisi's in North Richardson.

I love Freebirds. I've been going for the past 15 years.  Wish they didn't change the recipe for the sauce,  because the hot sauce is NOT HOT AT ALL.  It user top button my lips,  not I'm disappointed.  I know there's another but,  Judy not the same.

Monster is a real monster...full meal n then some,all the food groups, everyone enjoyed the dinner out.
Nice choice if you are a little or if you need a full size monster for your appetite
A must try! The convenience of ordering online and picking up at the window was awesome! I have absolutely no complaints about portions or quality. Customer service was outstanding. Thank you.
Decent price, good food. Drive-thru makes it easy to pick-up. Lately, I always have a good experience here.

Passing through college station ... because of the Austin, TX vibe it has, we stopped. The staff was friendly and very helpful. The food, honestly,  liked it better than Chipotle, it was more authentic and flavorful.

The parking lot is a but chaotic. The servers stations are ill placed and easily disturb guests. However, the food is amazing. Full of flavor, and hearty. You get a lot of food for the money and the drinks are good. Servers are attentive, and nice. Nice atmosphere with the acoustic guitarist singing throughout the restaurant.

Popular restaurant in Oak Cliff serving Mexican dishes and specializing in seafood. Lunch specials available for the weekday business crowd with daily specials. Interesting space that is comprised of mutiple rooms of varying sizes that seem to meander. Part of the building may have been a house and architectural features remain. Table seating with white table cloths and napkins. Nice covered patio wraps around front and side of building. Generous drink sizes and happy hour specials. Friendly professional uniformed staff. Can accommodate larger groups. Reservations suggested for groups. Reason prices. Friendly hostess will seat you .
This was my second time there and it was much better than the first.  Food was great.  Service was mediocre.  Margaritas were good.  There's better Mexican food in Oak Cliff, though.
Great food, atmosphere and professuinal service. Try the fish soup and make sure to squeeze the lime in the soup-amazing. My first time trying fish soup and I loved it.
Great authentic Mexican seafood! We love it everytime we go! They started off in a small house and expanded the space and the parking. Pictured is the paella and the Plato especial.

Have heard previous terrible reviews of this place, but it's actually quite nice! Definitely go on Thursday since they have 3 dollar margaritas! And oh man are they delicious. I also had the fish tacos and those were so filling and delicious for only $9! Overall very happy I ignored my friends and came here.

We love blue goose!!!  Their chips are my favorite - thinner and lighter rather than the real thick heavy yellow ones.  Also, their queso is delicious.  Again, a little thinner rather than the real thick stuff.  And the beef fajitas are my favorite!  They give you a pretty big portion even on the fajitas for one so it’s really plenty for two people.  And the tortillas are excellent - and made fresh!  The meet is so tender and really well flavored.  Good atmosphere and good service!

Had dinner early on a weeknight, out on the terrace on mild day. Classic Mexican cuisine.well prepared and fresh. Starter chips and salsa usually predict the quality of of the main course, and theirs did not disappoint. Flour tortillas are definitely fresh, with the oven in view spiraling them along. Waitstaff was friendly and timely, and food was served in short amount of time. Not sure how a busy lunch hour or Friday night would be, but expect that food quality and service would meet the demand.

The place was nice and clean. Not loud. We order on the lunch special the sour cream chicken enchiladas with tortilla soup. Came out hot and very flavorful. 
The service was prompt and friendly. Pleasant experience.

Service at lunch is great! We were helped right away and they kept our bowl of complimentary chips always full! Some might say their salsa is a little spicy, but I thought it was perfect. The prices for the food are reasonable, but $2.95 for unsweetened tea seemed steep, even if they kept it full. We will return to eat here again.

This place is beyond amazing. Great food Yes! Not only do they have great food but the customer services is Immaculate. This place is very accommodating.  I really recommend Al Biernat’s. Eddie, brad and Dave thank you for making us feel welcomed

Out standing. Simply the best place to go and enjoy a high level of service parred with fantastic food. We had a wonderful date night without our kiddos. So thank you for a great experience. We will definitely be back soon.

Classy place. From the moment we pulled up we could tell that we were going to enjoy this meal. Well lit, but not too bright. Amazing food! The seafood platter was incredible (although a little on the pricey side). Steak was perfectly done. Shrimp and scallops we perfectly seasoned in a Thai inspired dish over coconut rice. Even the carrot cake at the end didn't disappoint. We will definitely be back.

Luxurious dining at it's best. Begin your experience with valet parking the doors opened for you to a beautiful dining room. For a Friday night you can still have a wonderful evening and conversation. Tempura Shrimp is an amazing starter and the Bone in Ribeye is cooked to perfection! Our server recommend the coconut cream pie.... every bit was worth the calories (so yummy). Perfect evening to enjoy for any occasion.

Just enjoyed the end of the month mixer on Thursday.   While my connection did not show until 8.  Plenty of other opportunities.

Definitely high end.  But, the atmosphere was right.
Awesome find! Great food and great service! Scallops sushi was just mind blowing. Ginny at the bar was incredible. Gave us awesome recommendations for menu items and drinks. Great conversation too.
Atmosphere is good. The servers are hard of hearing with the ambient noise so you may have to enunciate more than normal if you need something. It's petty but I noticed a pattern.
Service was good, food was great. Restaurant is clean and has a distinctively and refreshingly modern aesthetic. Pricey, but definitely worth a try if you like sushi and other asian fusion food.
There is good sushi and then there is next level sushi.  Shinsei has to be one of the best sushi spots in Dallas. Yes, they have rotating selection of cotton candy.
Great menu, food is delicious! Randomly found this place, and it was a gem.  Loved the decor.  Very cozy yet laid back fun atmosphere. Staff was very upbeat and sushi chef is amazing
Incredible. Great projector and friendly staff.

First off... complementary truffle salt popcorn! Secondly, your own water carafe. I went for brunch on Sunday and had the Texas s'mores waffle because Sweet Tooth of course. A Texas waffle with hand-made graham cracker , dark chocolate, and giant marshmallow and powdered sugar. Very casual atmosphere. Would definitely return

Good sport and great evening atmosphere. The service was good and the food came out hot and in a good manner of time. The drinks were ok and somewhat disappointing as they were not strong and appeared stingy on the liquor. Went there on a morning brunch and it was outstanding this time around the food was ok. Will come back to try out other options
American food at this spot - super tasty. The staff was friendly and observant. This place has an awesome atmosphere. Like a restaurant in Washington I loved.
Went with a group of 10 for dinner and drinks. Atmosphere was nice, and enjoyed our drinks. The food was good for the most part but a little on the pricey side.

Went in for Sunday brunch, found a mixed bag. Dining room was crowded though not full, took a couple seats in the bar area and had a bloody Mary that was truly great, though small. It was so good, and so small, I ordered a second one. Ordered the egg and pork nachos app to split. Delicious! But it took forever to get to us. The service through out the meal was sub par. Felt like we were forgotten. Then after another long wait we got our chicken fried steak and eggs. Potatos were great, the eggs were just about perfect, but the steak was underdone for CFS, and it was both over tenderized and too grizzly. Poor service and mixed food reviews will knock this iconic Oak Cliff kitchen out of the race with all the top notch competition in this neighborhood.

We visited this Cafe for the first time on what seem to be one of their busiest days (Sunday)!!!  The lines were very long and it was super crowded.  We had a huge take out order. So they rerouted all take out orders to the other side of the restaurant, instead of having us wait in the main order line, which was much more accommodating and it seem to make everything move along faster and smoother!!!  At that point they had me fairly impressed. Then came our turn to place our order, which I previously stated was quite hefty, but there was no problem at all!!!  They had at least two or three people at the counter to take the orders, so that no one had to wait on those of us who had large orders and took a lot of time doing so!!!  We placed our order and waited patiently, which didn't take as long as we had expected!!!  When our order was ready they took the time to check each and every order by what was on the order ticket, mind U our order was broken down into two separate tickets. When I tell U that we received each and everything we had ordered, I was really impressed!!!  
I would just like to thank South Dallas Cafe for the exceptional service that we received, for accommodating us so well and all while doing it with a smile and being very friendly!!!  Ur whole staff made an impression on me that day and I must admit I'm not one to easily impress at all!!!  I will recommend Ur establishment to anyone who's looking for great service and a damn good meal...the food was good and very satisfying!!!  When I'm in town, South Dallas Cafe will always be my go to from now on...for excellent service and great food!!!  Thank U again and keep up the great work...establishments such as this are hard to come by these days!!!

Went to Dallas Texas for spring break and wanted soul food since we don't really have any soul food places in Minnesota. My cousin lives in Dallas so he recommended this place. We went on a sunday and it was packed but the wait didn't seem long. It's buffet style but the workers serve you. I ordered the ribs, greens and mac and cheese. The mac and cheese was good but the greens and ribs were nasty and they give you this dry, hard cornbread muffin that had no taste to it. Seating was confusing. I had to get somebody to help us find a seat. For a minute it looked like we would have to stand there holding our trays until an empty table was available. I would not eat there again. 2 stars for the price and mac and cheese

My church family and I came to dine after service. The food was excellent! We had great food and fellowship. The staff was very kind and courteous. They were able to accomodate our large group as well. We were stuffed and ready for Sunday naps when we left. Thank you so much for your generosity, South Dallas Cafe❤.
Awesome soul food place! Nice and clean inside with friendly staff. And they had Live Jazz when we went!

South Dallas Cafe had been recommended for great soul food. I was really disappointed based on the bland taste of virtually everything that I ordered. Meat loaf, red beans, collard greens and even cornbread. Nothing tasted like the soul food I was raised on back in New York.
My top scene for bbq. service is always nice even when they have a full house. looking forward to coming back with my coworkers. the place has a good atmosphere.
Not to good interms of service . the food pretty normal taste . i can say i will find another better restaurants!
Lost business because of store hours not being listed correctly.
Dallas Texas! Pretty tasty bbq and brisket for a commercial chain with good customer service
Horrible service and attitudes from employees, food is not good at this location spend your money somewhere else!
Situated in the heart of city.Awesome place to hangout with friends. Friends can sit together for long time . Burgers are awesome in taste. All food items are good in taste.
Love to come here, after my coaching classes. It is very nice place for sitting with friends
Well !!!! Who doesn’t know abt Mcdonald 😄❤️ and i think 90% foodies will prefer to take a quick hunger break here. I request those 10% to fill the gap sooner the better 🔥 🔥🔥

It is situated in the Atlantis mall Civil lines......Prayagraj...... 
You all are well aware of the fact that it is a place mostly crowded.... it promotes self service.... the menu is being displayed on the screen above counters.... very limited items are there in this mcD Allahabad...  but it will be freshly prepared and served hot.... drinking water is available for free but one have to ask for it..... its affordable...... one cannot have a cosy atmosphere or a silent atmosphere since its generally over crowded....

I recommend you to taste ice creams...

I would prefer KFC for burgers. But if u want something lite than you ho for it.
The place is always crowded. Try the mcflurry and allu ticki
